 11  /-!
 12  # Prime numbers
 13  
 14  This file deals with prime numbers: natural numbers `p ≥ 2` whose only divisors are `p` and `1`.
 15  
 16  ## Important declarations
 17  
 18  All the following declarations exist in the namespace `nat`.
 19  
 20  - `prime`: the predicate that expresses that a natural number `p` is prime
 21  - `primes`: the subtype of natural numbers that are prime
 22  - `min_fac n`: the minimal prime factor of a natural number `n ≠ 1`
 23  - `exists_infinite_primes`: Euclid's theorem that there exist infinitely many prime numbers
 24  - `factors n`: the prime factorization of `n`
 25  - `factors_unique`: uniqueness of the prime factorisation
 26  
 27  -/
 28  
 29  open bool subtype
 30  
 31  namespace nat
 32  open decidable
 33  
 34  /-- `prime p` means that `p` is a prime number, that is, a natural number
 35    at least 2 whose only divisors are `p` and `1`. -/
